This paper deals with the task solvability of mobile robot systems, which is a core topic in the field of robotics (cs.RO). It also involves the study of distributed algorithms and fault tolerance, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper uses mathematical models and proofs to analyze the solvability of the gathering problem, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper proposes a reduction scheme based on distributed BG-simulation, which is a technique used in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
